OL,6,FThe court heard Moore had "never been
OL,7,Fknown to show violent tendencies
OL,8,Ftowards anyone," but had become
OL,9,Fincreasingly paranoid in the weeks
OL,10,Fleading up to the attack, believing
OL,11,Fhis flat was under surveillance.
OL,13,F"It was perfectly understandable that
OL,14,Fno-one predicted how you were going to
OL,15,Fbehave that day," the judge said.
OL,17,FRichard Posner, prosecuting, said Mr
OL,18,FMayo was survived by his sister, who
OL,19,Fhad previously provided a statement
OL,20,Fdescribing his "positive character."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
